{
  "texts": [
    "The carrier of a I-complex K is the union of all coalitions in K Note that our definition of simplicial complex does not require that all singletons of I be coalitions, in other terms we do not require that the carrier of K be equal to I, as is the case in the classical definition.",
    "Note also that a coalition of a simplicial complex is classically called a simplex.",
    "Profiles and Parting functionsA profile of (I, A) is a function α ∶ I → P(A).",
    "The set of all profiles on (I, A), P(A) I, is denoted PROF(I, A).",
    "A parting map of (I, A) is a function ρ ∶ A → P(I)."
  ]
}